=== TASK ===
# Host Dashboard (Listings List)

## Overview
Create a Host Dashboard page that presents the host’s property listings in a clear, editorially refined interface. The page shows each listing with its publish status (Draft / Live), last updated timestamp, and actions to edit or view related inquiries. A prominent Create Listing CTA should be available. Include a quick stats panel summarizing inquiries, views, and the date of the last inquiry. The page must integrate with the existing authentication/authorization system (Guests, Hosts, Concierge) to ensure only authenticated Hosts can access and manipulate their own listings, while read-only access to related inquiries is allowed. All data retrieval and UI interactions must be resilient to null/undefined values per the runtime safety requirements.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A secure, host-facing dashboard that lists the host’s current property listings, each with its status (Draft or Live), last updated date, and quick actions.

Goals:
- Provide an at-a-glance view of all host listings with filter capabilities (Draft / Live), sorting, and a prominent create action.
- Display a read-only inquiries summary per listing (e.g., total inquiries, last inquiry date, and a compact trend indicator) without exposing editing capabilities for inquiries from hosts.
- Maintain session persistence and role-based access control so only Hosts can access this page; Concierge has admin-level access to read related data if needed elsewhere.

Connected features:
- User Authentication & Authorization: Secure email/password authentication with session persistence, email verification, password reset, and role-based access control for Guests, Hosts, and Concierge.
- Listings management: Create/Edit Listing with image upload support, editorial content, and visibility toggle (Draft / Live).
- Inquiries (read-only): Read-only summaries related to each listing; accessible from the listing row.

UI elements and how they need to look:
- Listings Table/Grid: Columns for Title, Status (Draft / Live), Last Updated, Actions (Edit, View Inquiries). Each row should show a thumbnail image, listing title, meta (location/destination), and status badge.
- Create Listing CTA: Prominent, bronze-gold CTA button positioned above or alongside the listings list.
- Draft & Live Filters: Filter bar to quickly switch between Draft and Live listings; multi-select or single-select as appropriate.
- Quick Stats Panel: A compact panel showing:
  - Total Inquiries across all listings
  - Total Views (aggregate)
  - Last Inquiry Date (most recent)
- Read-only Inquiry Summary: In the “View Inquiries” action or a collapsed panel per listing, show a read-only mini-summary: number of inquiries, last inquiry date, and status labels.

UI guidance:
- Maintain a premium editorial aesthetic with generous whitespace, strong typography, and warm, restrained color usage per the project’s design system.
- Use large imagery for listing cards, with clear typographic hierarchy for titles and metadata.
- Ensure responsive behavior: table becomes a card-grid on small viewports; actions remain accessible.

API integrations:
- No external APIs beyond the existing backend. All data is fetched from the project’s backend via standard REST/GraphQL endpoints or a Supabase-like client. Ensure all responses are properly validated and guarded against null results.

## Components to Build
- HostListingsPage
  - Props: user (current authenticated user), listingsData, statsData
  - State: filterStatus, searchQuery, sortKey, isLoading
  - Subcomponents:
    - ListingCard/GridItem
      - Props: listing
      - UI: thumbnail, title, location, status badge, lastUpdated, actions
      - Actions: Edit (navigates to listing edit form), View Inquiries (opens read-only summary)
    - QuickStatsPanel
      - Props: stats
      - UI: three stat tiles (inquiries, views, lastInquiryDate)
    - CreateListingButton
      - Props: none
      - UI: bronze-gold button
    - InquiriesSummary
      - Props: inquiriesForListing
      - UI: read-only mini-summary (count, lastDate, status chips)
- ListingEditForm (for draft/live toggle, image upload, content)
  - Note: This page is part of the broader host workflow; include fields for title, location, description, images, price (if applicable), publish status, and validation.
- AuthGuard
  - Ensures only authenticated users with role Host can access the Host Dashboard route; redirects Guests/Concierge appropriately.
- DataFetchors
  - fetchHostListings(hostId, options)
  - fetchListingInquiries(listingId) // read-only summaries
  - fetchHostStats(hostId) // aggregates for QuickStatsPanel

Technical details:
- Data shaping: Always guard against nulls; use data ?? [] for arrays, verify with Array.isArray before mapping.
- Result handling: Ensure response shapes are validated; const listings = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- State defaults: useState<Listing[]>([]) for listings, useState<InquirySummary[]>([]) for summaries, etc.
- Image handling: Accept optional image URLs; provide placeholder if missing.
- Accessibility: All interactive elements must be keyboard navigable; aria-labels on controls.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Routing:
  - /host/dashboard/listings -> HostDashboardListingsPage (protected by AuthGuard for role Host)
- UI Components:
  - Listings grid/table with responsive behavior
  - Status badges (Draft / Live) with accessible color contrast
  - Sorting controls (Status, Last Updated)
  - Filters (Draft / Live)
  - Create Listing button (bronze-gold)
  - Per-listing read-only inquiries summary (collapsible or modal)
- Forms:
  - Listing Edit Form with validation (title, location, required fields)
  - Image upload integration (with progress indicator and error handling)
  - Publish status toggle with confirmation
- State & Data Handling:
  - Fetch listings on mount; show loading skeletons
  - Use null-safe patterns: (listings ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(listings) ? listings.map(...) : []
  - Persist filter and sort preferences in localStorage for session continuity
- Styling:
  - Implement per Visual Style guidelines including color palette, typography, and card design
  - Card hover states with bronze-gold accents
- Accessibility:
  - Keyboard focus states visible
  - Proper alternative text for images
  - Semantic HTML (tables or grids with appropriate roles)

### Backend
- API Endpoints (examples; adapt to actual stack):
  - GET /api/hosts/{hostId}/listings?status=Draft|Live&search=&sort=
  - GET /api/listings/{listingId}/inquiries (read-only summaries)
  - POST /api/listings (create listing)
  - PUT /api/listings/{listingId} (update listing, including publish status)
  - GET /api/hosts/{hostId}/stats (inquiries count, views, lastInquiryDate)
- Database Tables / Models:
  - hosts(id, user_id, ... )
  - listings(id, host_id, title, location, description, images, status ENUM('Draft','Live'), last_updated, views)
  - inquiries(id, listing_id, guest_id, created_at, status, message, ...) // read-only summaries
  - views(entity_type, entity_id, timestamp) or a simple views_count on listings
- Security:
  - Validate host ownership before allowing edit/view actions
  - Use role-based access control: Host can manage own listings; Concierge can access admin data; Guests restricted
- Validation:
  - Server-side validation for required fields; sanitize inputs; guard against SQL injection or injection in text fields
- Data safety:
  - Always check for nulls in responses; apply data ?? [] patterns

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - On page load, AuthGuard ensures Host access, then fetch host stats and listings
  - For each listing, fetch read-only inquiries summaries or fetch aggregated data in a batched call to minimize requests
  - QuickStatsPanel aggregates totals
  - Clicking Edit navigates to ListingEditForm with prefilled data
  - View Inquiries opens InquiriesSummary for that listing (read-only)
- Error handling:
  - Graceful UI when data is missing or API fails; show helpful empty-state UI and retry controls
- State synchronization:
  - When a listing is edited or created, refresh the listings list and stats

## User Experience Flow
1) Host navigates to /host/dashboard/listings and is authenticated as Host.
2) AuthGuard verifies permissions; page loads with a skeleton while data fetches.
3) QuickStatsPanel displays aggregate metrics (inquiries, views, last inquiry date).
4) Listings grid shows all host listings with title, location, status badge, last updated, and actions (Edit, View Inquiries).
5) Host uses Draft / Live filters to refine the list; can sort by Last Updated.
6) Host clicks Create Listing to open ListingEditForm or modal to create a new listing.
7) Host clicks Edit on a listing to modify details; can upload images; toggle status between Draft and Live with validation and confirmation.
8) Host clicks View Inquiries to see a read-only summary for that listing, including number of inquiries and last inquiry date.
9) On any changes, data refresh happens automatically to reflect the latest state.
10) If Host signs out, AuthGuard redirects to login; error states are clearly presented.

## Technical Specifications
- Data Models:
  - Host(id, user_id, name, email, ... )
  - Listing(id, host_id, title, location, description, images JSON, status ENUM('Draft','Live'), last_updated TIMESTAMP, views INT)
  - Inquiry(id, listing_id, guest_id, created_at TIMESTAMP, status, message)
  - ViewAnalytics(id, listing_id, timestamp)
- API Endpoints:
  - GET /api/hosts/{hostId}/listings?status=&search=&sort=
  - GET /api/listings/{listingId}/inquiries
  - POST /api/listings
  - PUT /api/listings/{listingId}
  - GET /api/hosts/{hostId}/stats
- Security:
  - JWT-based session/token management with refresh if applicable
  - Role-based access: Host can access their own listings; Concierge admin paths permitted
  - CSRF protection for state-changing requests
- Validation:
  - Frontend: required fields, max lengths, image upload limits
  - Backend: server-side validation and authorization checks
- Runtime Safety:
  - Always use data ?? [] for arrays from API responses
  - Guard array operations with Array.isArray(...) where applicable
  - Initialize all array state with useState<Type[]>([]) defaults
  - Access nested properties with optional chaining
  - Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Host can view a listing list with Draft / Live status, last updated, and actions (Edit, View Inquiries)
- [ ] Create Listing CTA is prominently visible and creates a new listing with proper defaults
- [ ] Draft and Live filters work correctly and update the list result
- [ ] Quick Stats Panel accurately reflects total inquiries, total views, and last inquiry date
- [ ] View Inquiries shows a read-only summary per listing without edit capabilities
- [ ] Access control enforces Host-only access to this page; unauthorized roles are redirected
- [ ] All data handling uses null-safe patterns and guards against null/undefined values
- [ ] UI adheres to the defined visual style, with responsive behavior and accessible components

